This is a '''timeline of [[w:Slack (software)|Slack]]''', a [[w:Cloud computing|cloud]]-based set of team [[w:Collaborative software|collaboration tools]] and [[w:online service|services]], founded by {{w|Stewart Butterfield}}.<ref name="SlackOpen">{{Cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/02/05/slacks-co-founders-take-home-the-crunchie-for-founder-of-the-year/ |title=Slack’s Co-Founders Take Home The Crunchie For Founder Of The Year |last=Kumparak |first=Greg |date=February 5, 2015 |website=TechCrunch |access-date=2015-04-10}}</ref>

==Big picture==

{| class="wikitable"
! Time period !! Development summary 
|-
| 2009 (January) – 2012 (December) || [[w:Glitch (game)|Glitch]] era. {{w|Tiny Speck}} is founded and launches the game, using {{w|Slack}} as an internal tool. {{w|Glitch}} would close in December 2012.
|-
| 2013 (August) onwards || [[w:Slack (software)|Slack]] era. After the closure of [[w:Glitch (game)|Glitch]], {{w|Tiny Speck}} launches Slack as a real-time collaboration app and platform.
|-
| 2014 (August)  onwards || {{w|Slack Technologies}} era. Tiny Speck renames itself to Slack Technologies, Inc. Service collaboration consolidates with major startups such as {{w|LinkedIn}} and {{w|Dropbox}}. By 2015, Slack daily active users growth peaks. In 2017 Slack is declared the best startup of the year at the {{w|Crunchies}}. 
|-
| 2016 and 2017 || {{w|Facebook}} and {{w|Microsoft}} launch their own products to compete with Slack.  
|}

